======================================================================
 BENCHMARK: Snapshot Isolation - Reading while rows are locked
======================================================================

  This test holds an exclusive UPDATE lock on rows via an open transaction,
  then attempts to SELECT those same rows from a second connection.
  Without snapshot isolation the read BLOCKS (times out). With snapshot
  isolation (SQLThinkRS built-in) the read succeeds instantly.

  Enabled ALLOW_SNAPSHOT_ISOLATION on tempdb (active, waited 0ms)
  Seeded tempdb.dbo.PerfLock (3 rows)
  Holding exclusive lock on PerfLock (Id=1) via open transaction...

--- .NET SqlClient - SELECT under lock (READ COMMITTED, 3s timeout) ---
  [BLOCKED] Timed out after 3017.1 ms - read was BLOCKED by the lock

--- SQLThinkRS - SELECT under lock (SNAPSHOT isolation, built-in) ---
  [OK] Completed in 2.8 ms - read 3 rows INSTANTLY (not blocked!)
  Data returned (pre-update snapshot):

Id Name  Value
-- ----  -----
 1 Alpha    10
 2 Beta     20
 3 Gamma    30


  Lock released (transaction rolled back)

